SIMPLE: faulty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Faulty
<hw>Fault"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Containing
faults, blemishes, or defects; imperfect; not fit for the use
intended.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Created once⟦br⟧
So goodly and erect, though <qex>faulty</qex> since.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Guilty of a fault, or of faults; hence, blamable;
worthy of censure.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The king doth speak . . . as one which is <qex>faulty</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Sam. xiv. 13.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Faun</ent>⟦br⟧
